SUMMARY:Lancaster County Benefit Auction
DESCRIPTION:Experience the vibrant spirit of the annual Lancaster County Benefit Auction\, a day where community fellowship meets the thrill of the auction block. This local tradition brings people together for a memorable experience filled with lively bidding and incredible food\, all organized to benefit families facing rare genetic disorders at the Clinic for Special Children. \nThe auction features an expansive array of goods ranging from traditional carriages and carts to masterfully crafted quilts and household furniture. Attendees can browse a massive inventory of farm supplies\, hardware\, and professional-grade tools\, alongside outdoor furniture and a lush selection of shrubbery and plants. Whether you are searching for rare collectibles\, children’s toys\, or beautifully arranged theme baskets\, the variety ensures there is something for every interest.
URL:https://bird-in-hand.com/event/lancaster-county-benefit-auction-3/
LOCATION:Leola Produce Auction\, 135 Brethren Church Road\, Leola\, PA\, 17540\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bird-in-hand.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/BenefitAuction.jpg
END:VEVENT
